      "lastUpdate": 1750158164566,
      "notes": "<p align=\"center\">\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/start.png\" />\n\nIn this tutorial, you'll learn how to create <b>freeform haptics</b> using the Pen tool.\n\nThis workflow is ideal for intuitively designing short, simple effects, such as UI interactions.\n\nThe Pen tool allows for quick prototyping without the need for an audio track. You can also use it in your audio flow to quickly edit envelopes. \n\nLet’s get started!\n"
    },
    {
      "clipId": "08632602-5a8a-4c3d-8058-035336efbbc8",
      "name": "Getting Started",
      "audioAsset": {
        "channels": 1
      },
      "haptic": {
        "version": {
          "major": 1,
          "minor": 0,
          "patch": 0
        },
        "metadata": {
          "editor": "Meta Haptics Studio 2.0.0-beta.10",
          "source": "",
          "project": "Getting Started",
          "tags": [],
          "description": ""
