      "lastUpdate": 1750687387549,
      "notes": "The editor provides an infinite canvas, allowing you to draw freely. The length of your clip is defined by the position of the last set breakpoint. \n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/adjust.png\"/>\n\n<b>Tip:</b> \nFor more precise control over the clip length, you can specify the exact duration of your haptic clip by entering a value for the last breakpoint into the time input field in the Design tab. You can adjust the value by typing directly or using the arrow controls.\n\nNow, click on the last breakpoint and extend the envelope to 20.0.\n\n/newpage\n\nUse the <b>Clip Navigator</b> to move around your canvas. You can adjust what you see by dragging the handles to zoom in or out.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<video width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/navigator.mp4\" autoplay loop/>\n\nIf you've navigated far out on the canvas, you can quickly return to your envelope by clicking in a specific area in the Clip Navigator. The editor view will automatically jump back to that section."
    },
