      "lastUpdate": 1750687536196,
      "notes": "A haptic clip consists of two envelopes: <b>Amplitude</b>  and <b>Frequency</b>. You can start your freeform haptics by drawing either one first. \n\nTo learn more about envelopes, see the tutorial: **The Basics of Haptic Design**.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/toggleB.gif\"/>\n\nOnce you've finished drawing the first envelope, use the toggle to switch to the second.\n\n/newpage\nTo ensure both amplitude and frequency envelopes have the same duration, the shorter envelope is automatically extended to match the duration of the longer one. This is essential for seamless integration into your product.\n\nYou have two options when working on the second envelope:\n\n/newpage\n<b> Keep the default value: </b> \nTo adjust it, simply move the first point up or down along the vertical axis.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/adjustvalue.png\"/>\n\n\n<b>Draw custom envelope: </b> \nSelect the Pen tool and begin placing points on the canvas as you did with the first envelope.\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/secondenvelope.png\"/>\n\n/newpage\n\nNow, let’s draw the second envelope with a slightly different shape. \n\nTry creating a shape similar to the one below:\n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/secondshape.png\"/>\n"
    },
